    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-18T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-18T20:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.48/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="6" xml:id="d517fn6">This same message was sent to the
                        Ambassador in France in Department’s telegram No. 6353, Nov. 20, 1918, 4
                        p.m., with the addition of the following paragraph: “After conferring with
                        Colonel House, you will take such steps with the Czecho-Slovak National
                        Council as may seem to you desirable, cabling Department action
                        taken.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-18T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 18, 1918—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Department has received the following cablegram through the Swedish Legation
                    from the Government of Austria: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The city of Vienna is threatened with a coal famine. If shipments of
                            coal do not arrive within 15 days the lighting of the city will have to
                            be stopped. The consequences to public order and safety of persons and
                            property would be deplorable. There is coal in the coal fields of <pb
                                facs="0721" n="633" xml:id="pg_633"/> Bohemia and Moravia. The
                            Allied Powers and United States of America are asked to intervene in
                            order that regular and sufficient shipments be sent on to Vienna.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
